AYUSH Doctors shall not prescribe¬†tablets or¬†mixtures as cure for COVID-19, but only as¬†an immunity booster, observed Kerala High Court while disposing a PIL.

The bench comprising the¬†Chief Justice S. Manikumar and Justice Shaji P. Chaly¬†also directed the medical/Police Departments to monitor the action of AYUSH medical practitioners.¬†

 According to him, if Homoeopathic medicines were given to all, more particularly to the people in highly affected districts, to those who are under observation, isolation and quarantine, this type of situation would not have happened.

KEY POINTS : 

1) Schools/Educational institutions to remain closed till September 30 for regular classes.

effect from 21st September 2020.

4) Cinema halls, swimming pools, entertainment parks, theatres (excluding open air theatre) and similar places not permitted to open.

5) No international air travel of passengers, except as permitted by MHA.

6) Though regular classes are not permitted till September 30, States/ UTs may permit upto 50% of teaching and non-teaching staff to be called to the schools at a time for online teaching/ tele- counselling and related work.

7) Students of classes 9 to 12 may be allowed to visit schools outside Containment Zones with parents' written consent.

8) There shall be no restriction on inter-State and intra-State movement of persons and goods. No separate permission/ approval/ e-permit will be required for such movements. 

9) States not to impose any local lockdown outside Containment Zones 

10) State/ UT Governments shall not impose any local lockdown (State/ District/ sub- division/City/ village level), outside the containment zones, without prior consultation with the Central Government.
